	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			       I camped the Kobold camps from level 4 to level 6, and regular Kobolds do have loot.  They drop basic Onyx earrings, copper bands (Rings) and once in a while a copper amulet.  They also drop basic alcohol, mostly short beers but I have gotten a mead or two from them.  The jewelery sells for a little money, and the beer for even less.  I find that the Kobold camp near the Druid Ring in Steamfont is a great place, as there is one Kobold that spawns up on a hill all alone, and 3 in the camp.  Beware though, Kobold Shamans spawn once in a while (You can't miss them, they are easily a foot taller than the rest), and they can put a damper on your day pretty quick, they have a fairly wide range of spells, considering that they are Kobolds  =)  (I have seen them cast low fire and ice spells, a -speed spell and once in a while they will Sicken you)
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
									
